just_use claude_issues.go

# label: SPIKE (ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack)
# role: Gopher view — file-backed issue tracker

A lightweight issue tracker for things Steve has asked
Claude to do. File-backed (no database): each issue lives at
`claude_issues/NNN-slug.md` with a tiny frontmatter block +
markdown body. The server reads these files on every
request; Claude edits them as work progresses.

## Why file-backed

Two benefits:
1. Steve can grep the tracker from the shell, or edit in
   his editor, or browse via `/gopher/wiki/gopher/claude_issues/`.
2. Git history IS the audit log. No separate events table.

## Routes

- `GET /gopher/claude-issues` — index page. Lists active
  issues (open / in-progress) as a sortable table, plus the
  last 10 shipped (done). Includes a `<details>` "File a new
  issue" form at the top.
- `POST /gopher/claude-issues` — from the inline form.
  `handleNewIssue` allocates the next ID and writes a new
  `claude_issues/NNN-slug.md` with open status. (Details in
  `handleNewIssue` — not read in this sidecar pass.)
- `GET /gopher/claude-issues/<id>` — detail page. Renders the
  issue's markdown body via `RenderMarkdown` if available,
  else a `<pre>`. Shows status badge + metadata + link to
  the wiki view of the underlying file.

## Frontmatter shape

Each `NNN-slug.md` starts with `---`-delimited frontmatter:
`id`, `title`, `status` (open / in-progress / done),
`source`, `created`, `updated`. Parser: `parseClaudeIssue`.

## Audience

Steve first, Claude second. The status badges (`open`,
`in-progress`, `done`) are visual cues for Steve scanning
the list; Claude edits status as work moves.

## Replaces

The hand-maintained `FIXES.md` used to live in the wiki.
Auto-maintained shipped-list here replaces it.

## Pointers

- Part of: ANCHOR_COMMENTS stack
  (`project_anchor_comments_stack.md`).
- Detail-page integration: `RenderMarkdown` function
  injected from wiki renderer.
- Status badge helper: `statusBadge(s)` (SPIKE issue #10 —
  dedicated detail page).
- Storage dir: `claude_issues/` at repo root.
